}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>Last Updated: @ViewData["UpdatedDate"]</p>

<h2>Welcome to TicTacTwo!</h2>
<p>Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to being transparent about how we collect, use, and protect your information. This Privacy Policy explains how our website operates regarding saved games, passwords, and game data.</p>

<h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
<p>We collect and store the following types of data to provide game functionality:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Game Data:</strong> Saved games and game states information are stored in our database. This data is used to allow players to continue their games or resume activity after leaving the site.</li>
    <li><strong>Passwords for Joining Games:</strong> When a game is created, a password is generated to allow other players to join the game via a link. These passwords are not linked to any personal information and are stored securely in our database.</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. How We Use the Information</h3>
<p>The information collected is used strictly to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Enable players to resume saved games.</li>
    <li>Facilitate secure game joining using passwords.</li>
    <li>Improve the game experience by maintaining game functionality.</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Sharing and Security</h3>
<ul>
    <li>We Do Not Share Data outside the game (console or web)</li>
    <li>We implement appropriate technical measures to ensure that stored data (e.g., saved games and passwords) is protected. However, no system is 100% secure, and we encourage players to keep their passwords private.</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Cookies and Tracking</h3>
<p>We do not use cookies or any third-party tracking technologies on our website.</p>

<h3>5. User Responsibilities</h3>
<p>Players are responsible for keeping game passwords private and only sharing them with trusted individuals.</p>

<h3>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes to our website or applicable regulations. Updates will be posted on this page with the revision date.</p>

<h3>7. Contact Us</h3>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how your information is handled, please contact us at @ViewData["ContactInformation"].</p>

<p>Thank you for playing TicTacTwo!</p>
